      "span_text": "Previous study has demonstrated that transcription from densely methylated promoters can only be partially restored by 5-aza-2Ј-deoxycytidine treatment but can obviously be enhanced by cotreatment with an inhibitor of histone deacetylase.  Therefore, another mechanism, such as deacetylation change of JunB gene, may play some role in the inactivation of the CpG island of JunB gene in K562 cells.",
